==========================================================================

%^RED%^%^BOLD%^SYNTAX ::: %^RESET%^set_details( map_targ )

This function is present in all objects. It will setup the mapping passed
in the arguement map_targ for the details present inside the object.

set_details( ([ "leaf":"You notice a hint of the morning dew on the leaf",
               "stem": (: stem_function :),
               "petal";"You spot a hint of pollen on the petal" ]) );

You may have as many or as few entries in this function as you wish.
It can accept both strings and functions as values in the key:value pairs
on the mapping. Please see %^CYAN%^%^BOLD%^coding mappings%^RESET%^ for more help on mappings.

see also ::

set_detail, remove_detail, remove_details, query_detail, query_details

